mber regime of quasi-geostrophic\nRayleigh-B\\'enard convection. Instead, simulations are characterized by what\nmay be termed a \\textsl{non-local} CIA balance in which the buoyancy force is\ndominant within the thermal boundary layers and is spatially separated from the\ninterior Coriolis and inertial forces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Mar 2023 19:49:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-08"}
