{"id":"2303.03512","submitter":"Chixiang Chen","authors":"Chixiang Chen, Ming Wang, Shuo Chen","title":"An Efficient Data Integration Scheme for Synthesizing Information from\n  Multiple Secondary Datasets for the Parameter Inference of the Main Analysis","comments":"Contact Email: chixiang.chen@som.umaryland.edu","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"stat.ME","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/","abstract":"  Many observational studies and clinical trials collect various secondary\noutcomes that may be highly correlated with the primary endpoint. These\nsecondary outcomes are often analyzed in secondary analyses separately from the\nmain data analysis. However, these secondary outcomes can be used to improve\nthe estimation precision in the main analysis. We propose a method called\nMultiple Information Borrowing (MinBo) that borrows information from secondary\ndata (containing secondary outcomes and covariates) to improve the efficiency\nof the main analysis. The proposed method is robust against model\nmisspecification of the secondary data. Both theoretical and case studies\ndemonstrate that MinBo outperforms existing methods in terms of efficiency\ngain. We apply MinBo to data from the Atherosclerosis Risk in Communities study\nto assess risk factors for hypertension.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Mar 2023 21:44:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-08"}
