{"id":"2303.03740","submitter":"Andras Laszlo","authors":"Andras Laszlo and Zsigmond Tarcsay","title":"Wilsonian renormalization group flows are ordinary distributions","comments":"14 pages + 3 pages appendix","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th gr-qc math-ph math.MP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  In nonperturbative formulation of quantum field theory (QFT), the vacuum\nstate is characterized by the Wilsonian renormalization group flow of Feynman\ntype field correlators. Such flow is a parametric family of ultraviolet (UV)\nregularized field correlators, the parameter being the strength of the UV\nregularization, and the instances with different strength of UV regularizations\nare linked by the exact renormalization group equation / Callan--Symanzik\nequation (ERGE/CS). In this paper it is shown that a natural, mathematically\nrigorous generally covariant definition can be given for the space of such\nWilsonian renormalization group flows. It is also shown that the space of these\nflows have favorable properties, similar to that of ordinary distributions, and\nthat each ordinary distributional field correlator naturally generates a\ncorresponding flow. The main theorem proved in the paper is that in the special\ncase of bosonic fields over flat (affine) spacetime, the flows generated by\nordinary distributional field correlators saturate the space of Wilsonian\nrenormalization group flows. That is, Wilsonian renormalization group flows of\nsuch correlators always have a limit at the UV infinity as a distribution, and\nthe running of the entire flow can be reconstructed from this limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Mar 2023 08:56:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-08"}
